title.48: Mighty Thor I, Whom the Gods Would Destroy (Trade Paperback)

description.1: A battle for the entire universe is underway! With Emperor D'Ken threatening to destroy the universe while trying to utilize the power of the M'Kraan Crystal, the X-Men and the Starjammers discover a horrible truth - when the specific stars come into alignment, the crystal will become available to D'Ken...and with it, the universe!
description.2: A crisis of faith for the Devil of Hell’s Kitchen! Matt Murdock has left his legal career behind but he’ll soon come across people who need a lawyer more than they need a super hero! Also, in this issue: Wolverine of the X-Men is on the hunt for someone murdering mutants!
description.3: Gray Hulk and X-Factor reluctantly unite against the Hulkbusters!  Guest-starring Doc Samson and the Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.!
description.4: They once were sworn enemies, but now the Force and Iron Man are sworn allies against common foe, Justin Hammer. Hammer is filled with wrath and has a new team of super villains ready to do his bidding.
description.5: An untold tale of Thor's storied past in the Marvel U! The Hulk is on the rampage, but when Thor confronts him, the Jade Giant makes a strange request! Can Thor best the Hulk in hand-to-hand combat--without the might of Mjolnir?
description.6: Spider-Man emerges from his grave and stumbles into Kraven's mansion. From the newspapers scattered on the ground, Spider-Man learns that one of his impersonators has been attacking the town for two weeks.
description.9: Introducing the strangest new villain the Fantastic Four have yet to encounter! He's a living electronic image, unable to be hurt, and out for revenge! Can anything stop the evil of the mysterious Fasaud? The new FF's baptism of fire continues!
description.12: Ed Marks has his first brush with Agent Orange and its memorable.
description.17: It's the startling conclusion to Kraven's Last Hunt. After Kraven proves his superiority over Spider-Man, what is left for the hunter? You must read this shocking ending.
description.18: Zeus realizes that his blind rage has been unleashed on his son, Hercules. The Avengers manage to distract Zeus, while Hercules regains his senses. After Zeus apologizes and forbids humans from setting foot on Olympus, Prometheus returns the Avengers to the realm of mortals.
description.19: It's a "Baptism of Fire" for the new Captain America as he battles a militant right-wing group called the Watchdogs!
description.21: Kraven continues his masquerade as Spider-Man and decides to attack men involved in a heroin operation.
description.22: Mantis’ mysterious (and complex) origin revealed! Revived from the brink of death by the former Avenger, Silver Surfer agrees to help Mantis in her battle against the Elders. Surfer and Mantis vs. Ego the Living Planet!
description.23: Wonder Man's movie is premiering! All the West Coast Avengers have been invited! Trouble is - the Abomination plans to crash the celebration ... and trash all the West Coast Avengers!
description.26: Guest-starring Doctor Strange! Cloak and Dagger take on the monstrous Nightmare, while the New Defenders assemble their best.
description.27: Stranded by the SHI'AR! The X-Men find themselves surrounded by alien foes, with only one option - FIGHT! Guest-starring the STARJAMMERS, and featuring the first appearance of the Shi'ar Imperial Guard - along with the debut of fan-favorite Shi'ar strongman GLADIATOR!
description.28: Black Widow is back! The super spy is once again asking Daredevil for help to take down another rogue super solider, but will the two of them be enough to take down the cybernetic solider?
description.29: Hulk comes into conflict with the heroic mutants of X-Factor! Will Marvel's Merry Mutants prevail? And why is Hulk...gray?
description.30: Shellhead turns out to be just fine following last issues' climactic ending! The Force wants to go straight, and his employer Justin Hammer wants him dead. Does Iron Man possess enough power to save Force from the B-team of the new Blizzard, Backlash, and the Beetle?
description.31: Meet the Thor of the future! In the 24th century, the brave Dargo embraces the power of Mjolnir and defends the world from all manner of evil! But what happened to the true Thor? And why does Mjolnir stray from its new wielder?
description.32: Kraven battles a beast and beheads it with his bare hands. He digs a grave and goes to a coffin, realizing that he "must die soon," and picks up a replica of Spider-Man's costume...
description.35: The beginning of a brand new Fantastic Four! The Thing, Human Torch, Crystal of the Inhumans, and Ms. Marvel usher in a fantastic new era for Marvel's first super-team! And they'll do it by stopping the menace that is...Diablo!
description.37: Spider-Man lies buried while Kraven dons a Spider-Man costume to prove that he is the better of his foe in every way. Plus, what horrible crimes is the Vermin about to commit?
description.38: Avengers vs. Zeus! What's left of the Avengers, anyway! Following their godly battle, the "mysterious stranger" reveals himself as Prometheus, a fallen Titan of Olympus. Hercules is healed, and Zeus goes delusional with power.
description.39: The new Captain America undergoes basic training- and wait'll you see how tough it is! Guest-starring: the Taskmaster and the Blob!
description.41: A first Christmas away from home causes Cpt. Merita to reflect on life at home versus Vietnam.
description.47: Ken Connell, keeper of the Star Brand, is caught in the middle of a fight of love, jealousy, international espionage, and winter in the Swiss Alps. And to top it all off, he discovers that his best friend is perhaps his worst enemy!
description.48: Thor vs. Hercules! The heavens rumble as two gods do battle…for the love of one mortal woman!
description.50: Tormented by the death of a young boy he could not save, Ken Connell must come to grips with the fact that as great as the Star Brand power is— some forces in the universe are even greater. Guest-starring Nightmask!
description.51: Surfer hunts down The Collector seeking answers about his involvement in the Contest of Champions. What plans do the Elders of the Universe have for Galactus? Plus, the return of Espirita!
description.52: Can the West Coast Avengers defeat the deadliest villains of the Arizona desert?
description.53: East Coast vs. West Coast Avengers in a nice ol' game of softball. But of course, someone has to crash the party…
description.62: Encountering Eric the Red sneaking around the school, the X-Men preemptively strike only to get attacked from behind by Firelord!
description.63: Daredevil accidently gets an innocent New York City cab driver caught in the middle of a corrupt government power struggle. Can Daredevil save the innocent man before it’s too late?
description.64: The Stalker is out doing what he does best, but the Hulk is out too, and he does things little bit better...
description.65: Tony Stark discovers a shattering secret about himself and the people who depend on him most. Plus, an old and favorite friend returns to the Stark Enterprises office.
description.66: While visiting her beautiful sister, Lorelei, Amora the Enchantress reflects on her experience in the Secret Wars of Battleworld, and how she let the love of Thor tantalizingly slip through her fingers...
description.70: The return of Diablo! The FF's alchemy-wielding nemesis is back for revenge, but he'll have to face the new and improved team to get it! But who is the last new member of the Four?
description.73: A frantic plea for help from Mary Jane Watson in Pittsburgh plunges Peter Parker into the middle of a traumatic family crisis, and Spider-Man into a city-spanning fight for his life against the Spider-Slayer! Plus: Mary Jane Watson gives her answer to Peter Parker's proposal of marriage!
description.74: The Avengers must battle Pluto to reach the Pathway of Infinity. After reaching Olympus, the team attempts a negotiation with Athena, Hephaestus, and Venus. Wasp is captured by Artemis, who brings her before an enraged Zeus.
description.75: Who will be the next Captain America?
description.77: Corporal Marks and the men are assigned to security duty in Saigon, and learn what the local population really thinks about them.
description.78: Fat Cat's unruly behavior calls the attention of Bunsen. Plus, more Fat Cats emerge from the woodwork that leaves Spider-Ham scrambling to save the day!
description.79: After the Hulk rampages through a monolithic statue of Ben Grimm, a mega-monster battle breaks out! The Green Goliath and the Thing come to blows, but their duel is halted when both combatants are presented the opportunity to revert to their human forms...permanently.
description.80: Karma acts on the opportunity to use the Hellions to find her lost siblings!
description.81: Free to travel the cosmos, Surfer makes a triumphant return to Zenn-La. Once there, Norrin discovers that former love Shalla Bal is the newly minted ruler, and has restored the planet to its former glory! But is the romantic reunion too good to be true? Shalla Bal’s priorities have shifted, and Silver Surfer is a shadow of his former self.
description.82: The journey through Space-Time concludes! And Mockingbird makes a life-altering decision that will haunt her.
description.86: Another awe-inspiring X-Men epic retold - THE RETURN OF MAGNETO! How has the Master of Magnetisim escape from his impenetrable prison? And what is the connection between his escape and the mysterious Eric the Red? The X-Men might not survive long enough to find out!
description.87: When Black Panther arrives in New York City to deal with a former royal subject, Daredevil has no choice but to intervene.
description.88: Bruce Banner and Rick Jones go on a city wide search to find Betty Ross...
description.89: Tony Stark is back in his Iron Man armor and this time he's going to get the Ghost. The Ghost has sworn to destroy all corporations in the name of public service.
description.90: A giant-sized anniversary spectacular! The Frost Giants lay siege to Asgard, and only Thor can stop them...but he's stuck in the armor of the Destroyer! And only one person can possibly restore the Thunder God to his glory...his most hated enemy, the Prince of Evil himself, Loki!
description.94: Torch vs. Thing! With Reed and Susan leaving the team to raise Franklin, it's up to new leader Ben to choose who will fill the gaps! His first pick- Crystal of the Inhumans! But newlywed Johnny's not too pleased about having to work with an old flame!
description.96: FRIEND OR FOE? Spider-Man learns he can never trust Black Cat...and finally comes to blows with the Foreigner!

7.text: Boom-Boom is back and is the stowaway on the Right’s aircraft where they have Rusty, Skids, Leech and Artie held hostage!

10.text: Destiny senses a terrible fate for the X-Men-and the world! Meanwhile, Storm is forced to fight supernatural animals without the help of a debilitated Nazà©, and even encounters Forge...but are things really as they appear?

11.text: The first and second generation Morituri have escaped Earth in one of the Horde's ships. Have they gone to the other side? During the journey the team finds out that the hands of Morituri stretch out to affect more people than they thought.

13.text: The grand finale! Can the Fallen Angels band together to escape from captivity, and more importantly escape alive?

14.text: The Rev. Sammy Smith has amassed a dangerous following…so much so that he’s gained the attention of The Punisher! Frank Castle vs. a False God!

20.text: The Hellions lock horns with the New Mutants once again, this time over capturing the mysterious Bird Boy! But what sort of feelings do New Mutant Magma and Hellion Empath have for one another?

21.text: Kraven continues his masquerade as Spider-Man and decides to attack men involved in a heroin operation.

22.text: Mantis’ mysterious (and complex) origin revealed! Revived from the brink of death by the former Avenger, Silver Surfer agrees to help Mantis in her battle against the Elders. Surfer and Mantis vs. Ego the Living Planet!

23.text: Wonder Man's movie is premiering! All the West Coast Avengers have been invited! Trouble is - the Abomination plans to crash the celebration ... and trash all the West Coast Avengers!

26.text: Guest-starring Doctor Strange! Cloak and Dagger take on the monstrous Nightmare, while the New Defenders assemble their best.

28.text: Black Widow is back! The super-spy is once again asking Daredevil for help to take down another rogue Super-Solider, but will the two of them be enough to take down the cybernetic solider?

33.text: X-Factor is attacked by protesters at the will reading of the late Warren Worthington!

36.text: The X-Men are forced to repel the attacks of a mind-controlled Polaris, but will Havok be able to hurt someone so dear to him? Meanwhile, Longshot and Wolverine must stop an assassination attempt by Scalphunter!

40.text: The battle for Earth rages on! As the alien horde continues their relentless assault against Earth, emotions on the Strikeforce flare. Will the team be able to save their home once and for all?

43.text: The Angels are living it up on Coconut Grove, a planet that resembles the best of night clubs! Unfortunately, the rulers crash the party and take them captive…!

44.text: Frank Castle attempts to start anew in the American Midwest -- but this period of tranquility doesn’t last long!

45.text: Keith embodies the spirit of a snake-god to shake the faith of Tullius’ followers and to save his sister and friend!

47.text: Ken Connell, keeper of the Star Brand, is caught in the middle of a fight of love, jealousy, international espionage, and winter in the Swiss Alps. And to top it all off, he discovers that his best friend is perhaps his worst enemy!

48.text: Thor teaches Lady Sif what about Midgard—and its people—rings special and true.

49.text: The New Mutants go to a party celebrating the new album of Cannonball's girlfriend, Lila Cheney.  But things quickly go awry when aliens attack, and Cannonball is peer pressured into taking drugs!

50.text: Tormented by the death of a young boy he could not save, Ken Connell must come to grips with the fact that as great as the Star Brand power is— some forces in the universe are even greater. Guest-starring Nightmask!

51.text: Surfer hunts down The Collector seeking answers about his involvement in the Contest of Champions. What plans do the Elders of the Universe have for Galactus? Plus, the return of Espirita!

52.text: Can the West Coast Avengers defeat the deadliest villains of the Arizona desert?

53.text: East Coast vs. West Coast Avengers in a nice ol' game of softball. But of course, someone has to crash the party…

57.text: Meet the Bronx teenagers chosen for their extraordinary abilities, trained in hand-to-hand combat by the mysterious Mr. Mack until their strength and courage are forged as hard as steel. They are...the Wolfpack!

58.text: The Fallen Angels mourn the passing of their comrade, while the last two Multiple Men discuss merging into one, causing one to feel the pain of death in the process…

59.text: At stake? Everything Lucian holds dear! Voodoo priest Tullius sets out to ruin his twin brother, starting with his reputation and ending with his life! Nightmask comes face-to-face with Martine at last.

61.text: A tale of the Warriors Three! An upcoming wedding in Asgard leads to ripe trouble for Volstagg the Voluminous! Denied an invitation, Loki transforms the groom into a goat!

67.text: In confessional, Richard Fisk recounts his rise as the masked Rose to a priest. The legacy of Ned Leeds, and his stint as Hobgoblin, continues to haunt Spider-Man.

68.text: Rusty tries to prove his strength in an attempt to clean up Central Park, but ends up giving mutants an even worse rep.

71.text: Nazà© and Storm continue looking for Forge at the Grand Canyon. Meanwhile, the X-Men have taken off to San Francisco to protect Madelyne Pryor from the Marauders. All goes well...until one mind-controlled magnetic Marauder shows up!

76.text: As the alien horde mercilessly attacks Earth, the Strikeforce are left with very little hope to defend their home. Beaten and broken, what possible plans can the team create in order to save Earth?

79.text: After the Hulk rampages through a monolithic statue of Ben Grimm, a mega-monster battle breaks out! The Green Goliath and the Thing come to blows, but their duel is halted when both combatants are presented the opportunity to revert to their human forms...permanently.

80.text: Karma acts on the opportunity to use the Hellions to find her lost siblings!

81.text: Free to travel the cosmos, Surfer makes a triumphant return to Zenn-La. Once there, Norrin discovers that former love Shalla Bal is the newly minted ruler, and has restored the planet to its former glory! But is the romantic reunion too good to be true? Shalla Bal’s priorities have shifted, and Silver Surfer is a shadow of his former self.

82.text: The journey through Space-Time concludes! And Mockingbird makes a life-altering decision that will haunt her.

91.text: Wolverine, no stranger to grief, provides a shoulder of support when Spider-Man is overwrought by Ned Leeds' death.

92.text: Hank, Bobby, and Caliban run away from the police and directly into Apocalypse’s three Horsemen: War, Pestilence and Famine!

95.text: Storm tasks Wolverine with taking over as leader of the X-Men while she searches for Forge to get him to return her powers. But where is Forge, and why does Nazà© want to find him so badly?

97.text: In this issue, an Angel dies! And we won't tell you which one...

98.text: Frank Castle sets out to stop the drug dealers at their source!

99.text: Lucian faces one bump in the road after another when he heads to a dream research conference in New Orleans.
